race.comment: Tough race. JEALOUS (2) could be ready to fire third up. Two runs back have been rock solid, quickly to 2000m here second up in the Pinker Pinker Plate when midfield in a stronger race. She should be ready to peak now and while she doesn't win many, this looks a nice race for her. STORM AHEAD (3) was poor last time at Pakenham but had been coming along well prior, beaten half a length at Geelong two back. Lightly raced and he can bounce back with blinkers on. LOTS TO LOVE (6) stuck on fairly well at Sandown Hillside out to 2400m last time having broken the maiden at short odds prior. Back in trip here but can continue to progress and give a sight. COMPRESSING (1) was well beaten fresh at Moonee Valley over 1600m but will take plenty of improvement from that and the rise in trip is far more suitable. ART 'N' SOUL (5) is sharply up in trip second-up but looks to have come back well.
